{"lemma":"دَوْمُ","slug":"دَوْمُ","root":"د.#.م","root_slug":"د-_-م","root_link":"/words/roots/د-_-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13471"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D9%85%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to turn in a circle, to rotate, to spin, to twirl","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to turn, to rotate, to spin, to twirl (something)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of دَامَ (dāma) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Mediterranean fan palm (Chamaerops humilis)","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13471","headword_ar":"دَوْمٌ","root":"dwm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. of 1 [q. v.]. (S, M, Msb, K.) — [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA zaAlati Als~amaA='u dawomFA dawomFA","text_ar":"مَا زَالَتِ السَّمَا=ءُ دَوْمًا دَوْمًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sky ceased not to rain"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the manner of the rain termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diymap","text_ar":"دِيمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dayomFA dayomFA","text_ar":"دَيْمًا دَيْمًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K; [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diyomFA diyomFA","text_ar":"دِيْمًا دِيْمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) in which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is interchangeable with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) mentioned by AHn, on the authority of Fr. (TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAy^imN","text_ar":"دَايِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.       -A2-  Also [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cucifera Thebaïca;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Delile, “ Floræ Ægypt. Illustr., ” no. 941;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Theban Palm;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because abundant in the Thebaïs;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of fan-palm;"},{"kind":"text","text":"by some called gingerbread: accord. to Forskål, (under the heading of “ Flora Arabiæ Felicis, ” in his “ Flora Ægypt. Arab., ” p. cxxvi.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Borassus flabelliformis;"},{"kind":"text","text":"a name applied (after him) by Sonnini to the Theban palm; but now generally used by botanists to designate another species of fan-palm:] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tree of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqol","text_ar":"مُقْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a well-known kind of tree, of which the fruit is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqol","text_ar":"مُقْل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": AHn says that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dawomap","text_ar":"دَوْمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tree that"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"becomes thick and tall, and has"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leaves of the kind termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuwS","text_ar":"خُوص"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xwS","text_ar":"خوص"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the date-palm, and racemes like the racemes of a date-palm."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) Accord. to Aboo-Ziyád El-Aarábee, (AHn, M,) The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabiq","text_ar":"نَبِق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which properly signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fruit of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidor","text_ar":"سِدْر"},{"kind":"text","text":", but here app. means, as it does in the present day, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tree called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidor","text_ar":"سِدْر"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of lote-tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"called by Linn."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rhamnus spina Christi,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and by Forskal"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rhamnus nabeca,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is also thus called, (AHn, M, K,) by some of the Arabs: accord. to 'Omárah,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trees of the kind termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidor","text_ar":"سِدْر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AHn, M:) and, (M, K,) accord. to IAar, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"big trees of any kind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dawomapN","text_ar":"دَوْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.]"}],"source_refs":["TA","AHn","M","K"]}]}}